The name Marilyn Manson is formed by a juxtaposition of two opposing American [[cultural icon|pop cultural icons]]: [[Marilyn Monroe]] and [[Charles Manson]].<ref name="longhard">{{cite book |title=The Long Hard Road out of Hell |last=Manson |first=Marilyn |publisher=HarperCollins |year=1998|isbn=978-0-06-098746-6|pages=85–87}}</ref> Monroe, an actress, was one of the most popular [[sex symbol]]s of the 1950s and continues to be a major icon over 50 years after,{{sfnm|1a1=Chapman|1y=2001|1pp=542–543|2a1=Hall|2y=2006|2p=468}} while Manson, a cult leader, was responsible for [[Tate murders|the murder]] of actress [[Sharon Tate]], as well as several others; and served a [[life imprisonment|life sentence]] on murder and conspiracy charges until his death in 2017.<ref name="bugliosi">Bugliosi, Vincent with Gentry, Curt. ''Helter Skelter{{snds}}The True Story of the Manson Murders 25th Anniversary Edition'', W.W. Norton & Company, 1994. {{ISBN|0-393-08700-X}}. oclc=15164618.</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/nov/20/charles-manson-dead-cult-leader-sharon-tate|title=Charles Manson, US cult leader and convicted murderer, dies aged 83|last=Sidahmed|first=Mazin|date=November 20, 2017|work=The Guardian|access-date=November 20, 2017|language=en-GB|issn=0261-3077|archive-date=November 20, 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171120063205/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/nov/20/charles-manson-dead-cult-leader-sharon-tate|url-status=live}}</ref>

{{Quote box
 |quote = Manson was a [[culture war]] agitator for ''our'' side, someone willing to jar and frighten the fuck out of the power structures that seemed there to keep teenagers in their place&nbsp;... and his tactics made him a target, both of mass-culture disdain and of superior alt-culture snark. All that was by design. He put himself out there to take those attacks. And on some level, he's a saint for that.
 |source = —''[[Stereogum]]'' on Marilyn Manson.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stereogum.com/1693203/portrait-of-an-american-family-turns-20/franchises/the-anniversary/ |title=Portrait Of An American Family Turns 20 |last=Breihan |first=Tom |work=[[Stereogum]] |publisher=Valence Media |date=July 18, 2014 |access-date=February 10, 2019 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190209183525/https://www.stereogum.com/1693203/portrait-of-an-american-family-turns-20/franchises/the-anniversary/ |archive-date=February 9, 2019 }}</ref>
